cards.name: Eevee V

cards.name: Mew

abilities.name: Mysterious Tail
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may look at the top 6 cards of your deck, reveal an Item card you find there, and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

cards.flavorText: Its DNA is said to contain the genetic codes of all Pokémon, so it can use all kinds of techniques.

cards.name: Magnezone

abilities.name: Giga Magnet
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 6 cards of your deck and attach any number of Metal Energy cards you find there to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

cards.flavorText: Some say that Magnezone receives signals from space via the antenna on its head and that it's being controlled by some mysterious being.

cards.name: Miltank

abilities.name: Miracle Body
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon V.

attacks.name: Rout
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: Miltank produces highly nutritious milk, so it's been supporting the lives of people and other Pokémon since ancient times.

cards.name: Bidoof

abilities.name: Carefree Countenance
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

attacks.name: Hyper Fang
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

cards.flavorText: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

cards.flavorText: Fletchinder scatters embers in tall grass where bug Pokémon might be hiding and then catches them as they come leaping out.

cards.name: Cleffa

cards.name: Nidoran ♀

attacks.name: Poison Horn
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

cards.flavorText: It uses its hard incisor teeth to crush and eat berries. The tip of a female Nidoran's horn is a bit more rounded than the tip of a male's horn.

cards.name: Poliwhirl

attacks.name: Frog Hop
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

cards.flavorText: This Pokémon's sweat is a slimy mucus. When captured, Poliwhirl can slither from its enemies' grasp and escape.

cards.name: Weepinbell
cards.flavorText: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

cards.name: Tauros

attacks.name: Gather the Crew

attacks.name: Rage
attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

cards.name: Flareon

attacks.name: Destructive Flame

attacks.name: Fighting Blaze
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex or Pokémon V, this attack does 90 more damage.

cards.flavorText: Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

cards.name: Omanyte

attacks.name: Tentacular Return

cards.flavorText: This Pokémon is a member of an ancient, extinct species. Omanyte paddles through water with its 10 tentacles, looking like it's just drifting along.

cards.name: Dragonair

attacks.name: Aqua Slash

cards.name: Mewtwo

attacks.name: Reflective Barrier

attacks.name: Venomous Impact

ACE SPEC: You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

attacks.name: Leaf Litter Tackle
attacks.text: Discard a Grass Energy from this Pokémon.
